==English==

===Etymology===
* First attested in early 15th century.
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|accompanien}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|acompagner||to associate with}}, from {{m|fro|compaign||companion}}. See [[company]].

